.TH EDIT 1
.SH NAME
edit \- text editor with 9P interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wm/edit
.RI [ file ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Edit
is a Draw-based text editor for Inferno that runs under the
.IR wm (1)
window manager or any window manager providing a
.IR draw (3)
context.
It provides keyboard and mouse editing with undo, find, goto line,
selection, cut/copy/paste, and a scrollbar.
.PP
.I Edit
also serves a 9P filesystem interface for programmatic access by
Veltro agents and other tools.
The filesystem is mounted at
.B /mnt/edit
and bound to
.BR /edit/ .
.PP
If a
.I file
argument is given,
.I edit
opens it on startup.
.SS Keyboard
.TP
.B Type
Insert text at the cursor.
.TP
.B Backspace
Delete character before cursor, or join with previous line.
.TP
.B Delete
Delete character at cursor, or join with next line.
.TP
.B Enter
Split line at cursor.
.TP
.B Tab
Insert tab character.
.TP
.B Arrow keys
Move cursor up, down, left, right.
.TP
.B Home / End
Move to start or end of line.
.TP
.B Page Up / Page Down
Scroll by screenful.
.TP
.B Ctrl-A
Select all.
.TP
.B Ctrl-C
Copy selection.
.TP
.B Ctrl-F
Find (prompts in status bar).
.TP
.B Ctrl-G
Find next occurrence.
.TP
.B Ctrl-Q
Quit (saves if dirty and file has a path).
.TP
.B Ctrl-S
Save.
.TP
.B Ctrl-V
Paste.
.TP
.B Ctrl-X
Cut selection.
.TP
.B Ctrl-Z
Undo last edit.
.TP
.B Escape
Cancel selection or dismiss find/goto prompt.
.SS Mouse
.TP
.B Button 1
Place cursor or drag to select text.
.TP
.B Button 2
Paste from snarf buffer.
.TP
.B Button 3
Context menu: undo, save, find, goto line, select all,
cut, copy, paste, exit.
.TP
.B Scroll wheel
Scroll document up or down.
.SS Features
.PP
Long lines wrap visually at the window edge.
Tab characters are displayed as 4 spaces.
Line numbers are shown in the left gutter.
The status bar shows the file path, modification state,
and current line/column position.
.PP
The editor supports theming via
.IR lucitheme (2).
If a theme module is available, colours are loaded from it;
otherwise built-in defaults are used.
.SS 9P Filesystem
The filesystem layout uses per-document directories:
.PP
.EX
/edit/
    ctl          Global control (open, new, quit)
    index        List open documents
    1/           Per-document directory
        body     Read/write document text
        ctl      Document control (save, goto, find, etc.)
        event    Blocking read for editor events
        addr     Cursor position (line col)
.EE
.PP
Writing to
.B /edit/ctl
supports commands:
.BR open " path,"
.BR new ","
.BR quit "."
.PP
Writing to
.B /edit/1/ctl
supports commands:
.BR save ","
.BR "goto N" ","
.BR "find text" ","
.BR "name path" ","
.BR clean ","
.BR dirty ","
.BR "insert line col text" ","
.BR "delete sl sc el ec" "."
.PP
A real-file IPC interface at
.B /tmp/veltro/editor/
is also maintained for cross-namespace access by the Veltro
.I editor
tool.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B /dis/wm/edit.dis
Compiled editor.
.TP
.B /mnt/edit
9P mount point.
.TP
.B /edit/
Bind point for 9P filesystem.
.TP
.B /tmp/veltro/editor/
Real-file IPC directory.
.SH SOURCE
.B /appl/wm/edit.b
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR wm (1),
.IR acme (1),
.IR draw (3),
.IR wmclient (2),
.IR lucitheme (2)
